The official Google Ads MCP server is a Python-based, read-only implementation maintained by Google that allows AI agents to interact with the Google Ads API [1][2]. It provides essential tools for account discovery, metadata retrieval, and GAQL-based searching [1][3].

To use it, add the following configuration to your MCP client's settings file [2]:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "google-ads-mcp": {
      "command": "pipx",
      "args": ["run", "--spec", "git+https://github.com/googleads/google-ads-mcp.git", "google-ads-mcp"],
      "env": {
        "GOOGLE_PROJECT_ID": "YOUR_PROJECT_ID",
        "GOOGLE_ADS_DEVELOPER_TOKEN": "YOUR_DEVELOPER_TOKEN"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Several third-party MCP servers also exist, such as those by mharnett, FGRibreau, and others, which often include additional capabilities like write operations, campaign management, and built-in safety guardrails [4][5][6]. Requirements typically include a Google Ads developer token and OAuth 2.0 credentials [2][4][5].
